Description.SourceString: A conceptual model of The Entity. The light rusting may be intentional.
A conceptual model of The Entity. Though the metal remains strong, it rings hollow within.
A conceptual model of The Entity. Though lacking magnetism, the carving attracts itself to certain people.
A conceptual model of The Entity. Though beautiful, it evokes anxiety in those who hold it.
Memorabilia from an ambitious, yet doomed-to-fail, social media company.
A highly controversial statement that yes, pineapple belongs on pizza.
An acoustic guitar, perfectly tuned and engraved with flowers.
A hopeful songbird, Kate lifted others' spirits when all seemed lost.
A music note formed from mother of pearl, glittering with luminosity.
A grotesque trophy, taken from the remains of a cavalry unit.
A worn-down doll, soiled, reeking, and cherished above all.
A symbol of life, though from another perspective, it's the vessel that ferries one to death.
And so, as it ends, it begins.
A symbol of birth, life, and death. The finality of the waning moon seems incongruous in The Entity's realm.
A key to unlocking sacred wisdom or a trifling bauble?
Distributed to employees to boost morale in lieu of a bonus.
The critics agree: “Simulation Terror is a terror to read!”
The few who hold a remnant of hope and innocence believe it bestows luck.
Every great murder has a soundtrack.
There was a discordance to the damaged speakers that gave them a unique sound all to themselves.
A finely crafted container that stimulates a wisp of ever-changing Fog.
A relic that's incapable of measuring time in this realm.
The trinket of a child, alone, cold, and terrified.
The trinket of a teenager, searching for a morsel.
The trinket of a woman, taking fate into her own hands.
The trinket of a killer, stalking those who approach her home.
The trinket of a monster, asserting dominance over all in her forest.
With quiet confidence, Kate picked up the guitar.
Sometimes Kate's fingers missed a chord, but it didn't deter her.
Kate's voice had a natural cadence that made people want to listen.
Kate combined the guitar with her voice, as if it was a single part of her.
There was a spark of hope that Kate kept in her voice, wherever she went. It was of greater importance than she'd know.
Hello? The mobile realm awaits your sacrifice.
